  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">International Partnership Programme (see Programme details section for individual project summaries)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To undertake an analysis of requirements, stakeholders and data sources for a Sub-Saharan African crop risk monitoring and forecasting system. To identify the priority cropping systems, typical and forecasted pest risks and other influential biotic/abiotic threats. Scope an implementation project to develop a risk modelling and warning system. Identifying stakeholders including national governments; NGOs; Agro-industry representatives; and National Plant Protection Offices (NPPO) in the target countries.</narrative>
  </description>
